<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h3>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> There are ten pronunciations of <i>Islam</i> in English, differing in whether the first or second syllable has the stress, whether the <i>s</i> is pronounced <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/z/</span> or <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/s/</span>, and whether the <i>a</i> is pronounced as in <i>father,</i> as in <i>cat,</i> or when the stress is on the <i>i</i> as in the <i>a</i> of <i>sofa</i> (Merriam Webster). The most common are <small>IPA</small>: <span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" title="Wikipedia:IPA for English">/ˈɪzləm/, /ˈɪsləm/, /ɪzˈlɑːm/, /ɪsˈlɑːm/</a></span> (Oxford English Dictionary, Random House) and <small>IPA</small>: <span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" title="Wikipedia:IPA for English">/ˈɪzlɑːm/, /ˈɪslɑːm/</a></span> (American Heritage Dictionary).</li>
</ol>
</div>
